race.comment: Tricky. BLAKEMORE AVENUE (11) quickly returned to form winning this grade first up over 1200m at Beaudesert. He's been kept on the fresh side and fitter he can go on with it now. SON OF BEEBEE (8) has had a 43-day freshen-up and drops back from a mile. He's won and this course and over this distance and KWT replaces the 2kg apprentice. Will probably settle forward and feature. TAKUNAI (14) also comes back from a mile and has been kept on the fresh side. Found the grade a bit rich last time but the Warwick placing prior reads well enough. BLUE CHIP GIRL (5) has a wide barrier but isn't badly placed. Comes out of a form race at Warwick and has also been given a brief freshen. SHUT EYE (4) won't be far away if he puts his best foot forward.
